---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="DevToolsBox terms of service. Use our tools at your own discretion."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 prose prose-slate">
    <h1 data-i18n="terms.heading">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-600"><em><span data-i18n="terms.updated">Last updated:</span> {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", { year: "numeric", month: "long", day: "numeric" })}</em></p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.acceptTitle">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.accept">
      By using DevToolsBox, you agree to these terms of service. If you do not agree, please do not use our website.
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.serviceTitle">2. Service Description</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.service">
      DevToolsBox provides free online developer and utility tools. All tools are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We process all data client-side in your browser, meaning your input never reaches our servers.
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.userTitle">3. User Responsibilities</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.user">
      You agree not to use our tools for any illegal or unauthorized purpose. You must not misuse or attempt to disrupt our services.
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.ipTitle">4. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.ip">
      The content, design, and tools on DevToolsBox are protected by copyright. You may not copy, modify, or redistribute our tools without permission.
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.liabilityTitle">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.liability">
      DevToolsBox and its operators shall not be liable for any damages arising from the use or inability to use our tools. You use our services at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="terms.changesTitle">6. Changes to Terms</h2>
    <p data-i18n="terms.changes">
      We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
